Preparations for the third edition of the Nairobi Innovation Week that kicks off on Monday have been finalised.The week-long event, an initiative of the University of Nairobi, will bring together more than 100 local and international exhibitors, University of Nairobi vice chancellor Prof Peter Mbithi said on Monday.&ldquo;It is my hope and that of the University of Nairobi that delegates will get value for time. They will see, engage, learn and build new partnerships,&rdquo; he said.Mbithi spoke while receiving cheques from partners and sponsors of the event at the University of Nairobi Towers. They included KCB, Safaricom, Chase Bank, NIC Bank, Techno Mobile, Samsung, Uber and the University of Nairobi Alumni Association.